    <div class="summary">        
        <h3><a href="/questions/449030/mue0-rightarrow-mufe-mue" class="question-hyperlink">$\mu(E)&gt;0 \Rightarrow \mu(f(E))=\mu(E)$?</a></h3>
        <div class="excerpt">
            Consider injective continuous  functions $f:\mathbb{R}^2 \rightarrow \mathbb{R}^2$.

Which of these function are such that:

$\mu(E)&gt;0 \Rightarrow \mu(f(E))=\mu(E)$?

(Isometries are clearly ok.)

        </div>
             
